Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy was used to evaluate the oxide films formed on cobalt-coated Crofer 22 APU ferritic stainless steel after thermal oxidation at 800 degrees C in air for different times (i.e. 2, 50, 100 and 500 h).
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy

Sentencas: Impedance spectra of the oxide films exhibited two or three semicircles depending on the oxidation time, which correspond to the presence of two or three individual oxide layers.
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy

Sentencas: Coupled with scanning electron microscopy/energy-dispersive spectroscopy (SEM/EDS) and X-ray diffraction (XRD), the individual oxide layer corresponding to each semicircle was determined unambiguously.
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy

Sentencas: Impedance spectrum analysis of the oxide films formed on the sample after thermal exposure at 800 degrees C in air for 2 h led to the identification of the low-frequency and high-frequency semicircles as being from Cr2O3 and Co3O4, respectively.
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy

Sentencas: SEM/EDS and XRD analysis of the 500-h sample clearly revealed the presence of three oxide layers, analyzed to be Co3-xCrxO4, CoCr2O4, and Cr2O3.
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy

Sentencas: Although the SEM images of the 50-h and 100-h samples did not clearly show the CoCr2O4 layer, impedance plots implied their presence.
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy

Sentencas: The oxide scales were assigned to their respective semicircles and the electrical properties of Co3-xCrxO4, CoCr2O4 and Cr2O3 were determined from the impedance data.
Titulo: Impedance spectroscopy of the oxide films formed during high temperature oxidation of a cobalt-plated ferritic alloy
